quran[11]{c,v,t,f}:
32,1,"Alif. Lam. Mim."
32,2,"This Book, beyond all doubt, was revealed by the Lord of the Universe. {1}",footnotes:1:Several Surahs of the Quran begin with one or the other such introductory sentence
32,3,"Or do {1} they say: “He has fabricated it?” {2} Nay, it is the Truth from your Lord so that you may warn a people to whom no warner came before you; {3} perhaps they will be guided to the Right Way. {4}",footnotes:1:This is not merely a question but also an expression of great surprise and astonishment. It means to imply this: In spite of all those things on account of which this Book is
32,4,"It is Allah {1} Who created the heavens and the earth and all that is between the two, in six days, and then He established Himself on the Throne. {2} You have no guardian or intercessor other than He. Will you, then, not take heed? {3}",footnotes:1:Now the second objection of the mushriks which they raised against the Prophet’s (peace be upon him) message of Tauhid
32,5,"He governs from the heaven to the earth and then the record (of this governance) goes up to Him in a day whose measure is a thousand years in your reckoning. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
32,6,"He knows {1} all that is beyond as well as all that is within a creature's sense-perception. He is the Most Mighty, {2} the Most Compassionate, {3}",footnotes:1:That is
32,7,"He Who excelled in the creation of all that He created. {1} He originated the creation of man from clay,",footnotes:1:That is
32,8,"then made his progeny from the extract of a mean fluid, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
32,9,"then He duly proportioned him, {1} and breathed into him of His spirit, {2} and bestowed upon you ears and eyes and hearts. {3} And yet, little thanks do you give. {4}",footnotes:1:“Fashioned him”: developed him from a microscopic organism into a full-fledged human being and perfected him with limbs and other organs of the body.|180328:This is a fine way of saying something. Before the mention of “breathing into him of His spirit”
32,10,"They say: {1} “Shall we be created afresh after we have become lost in the earth?” Nay, the fact is that they deny that they will meet their Lord. {2}",footnotes:1:After answering the disbelievers’ objections about the prophethood and Tauhid
32,11,"Tell them: “The angel of death who has been charged with your souls shall gather you, and then you shall be brought back to your Lord.” {1}",footnotes:1:That is
